HEADWORD: Celebration
<hw>Cel`e*bra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>celebratio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act, process, or time of
celebrating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His memory deserving a particular <qex>celebration</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Clarendok.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Celebration</qex> of Mass is equivalent to offering Mass</q>
<rj><qau>Cath. Dict.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To hasten the <qex>celebration</qex> of their marriage.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Celebrator</ent>⟦br⟧
